%%{init: {'theme': 'base', 'themeVariables': {'actorBkg': '#F3E5F5', 'actorBorder': '#6A1B9A', 'signalColor': '#333333', 'fontSize': '13px'}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as OAuth Client
    participant TE as Token Endpoint
    participant CAM as Client Auth<br/>Middleware
    participant GH as Token Exchange<br/>Grant Handler
    participant TV as Token Validator
    participant TS as Token Service

    rect rgb(243, 229, 245)
        C->>TE: POST /oauth2/token<br/>grant_type=...token-exchange<br/>subject_token, subject_token_type,<br/>audience, resource, scope<br/>+ Client authentication
    end

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        TE->>CAM: Client Auth Middleware
        CAM-->>TE: Client authenticated

        Note over TE: Validate token_exchange<br/>grant allowed for app
        TE->>GH: ValidateGrant + HandleGrant

        GH->>TV: ValidateSubjectToken(subject_token)
        Note over TV: Verify JWT signature + expiry<br/>Validate issuer<br/>Audience checked only for<br/>auth assertions (assurance claim)
        TV-->>GH: Subject token claims

        opt actor_token provided
            GH->>TV: ValidateSubjectToken(actor_token)
            Note over TV: Same validation as subject
            TV-->>GH: Actor token claims
        end

        Note over GH: Scope: if none requested<br/>inherit from subject token.<br/>If requested, intersect.

        Note over GH: Audience priority:<br/>audience > resource ><br/>subject_token.aud > client_id

        GH->>TS: BuildAccessToken
        Note over TS: sub = subject_token.sub<br/>act = {sub: actor, iss: ...}<br/>aud = resolved audience

        TS-->>GH: Access token (JWT)
        GH-->>TE: Token response

        Note over TE: No refresh token,<br/>no id_token for exchange
        TE-->>C: 200 OK<br/>{ access_token,<br/>  issued_token_type,<br/>  token_type: Bearer }<br/>Cache-Control: no-store
    end
